United Democratic Alliance party Chairman Johnson Muthama's daughter Janet Nthoki has died. News of her death was first shared by Deputy President William Ruto on Tuesday. He described Janet as a person who will be remembered for her diligence, honesty and dependability. "Our love and prayers to UDA Chairman Johnson Muthama for the loss of his dear daughter Janet Nthoki Nduya. She was a diligent, responsible and honest lady who will be fondly remembered for her kindness and dependability," the DP tweeted. The second in command condoled with the family of the former Machakos senator. "May the family, relatives and friends find the strength to get through this pain. Rest In Peace, Janet."